description.value: Fragment of a vessel (cup?) with incuse (sunk) relief design in three layered cameo glass which is translucent blue, opaque white and translucent blue.  The white sunk relief design is an Egyptianising scene which shows the following. At the top, a uraeus (sun disc) flanked by feathers, perhaps part of a continuous decorative band.  Below this, a kneeling figure offers an Egyptian u-shaped wesekh collar (ceremonial collar), with one surviving floral terminal, to a deity. The right hand and wrist of the offrand are preserved, as are his knees, partly covered by a decorated skirt. He kneels on a step or platform in front of the god. Only one hand of the god survives, holding a sceptre.three-layered cameo glass.
